Your code does not contain a `DataSource` bean, nor is Spring providing any because you&#39;re excluding `DataSourceAutoConfiguration.class`. This is a problem, because the [`JpaRepositoriesAutoConfiguration`](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current/api/org/springframework/boot/autoconfigure/data/jpa/JpaRepositoriesAutoConfiguration.html) autoconfiguration is only invoked when a `DataSource` bean is present (it has a `@ConditionalOnBean`). 

The easiest solution is to re-enable `DataSourceAutoConfiguration` by removing the exclusion:

```java
@SpringBootApplication // Remove the `exclude` here
@RestController
@EnableTransactionManagement
public class PaymentgatewayApplication {
    // ...
}
```

After that, you can configure a `DataSource` bean with the `spring.datasource.*` properties and by providing the proper JDBC driver on your classpath.

